  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6772.96 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6775 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently long gamma and likely buying this dip given the -6.6% 1-minute move. The massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (+10.5B) creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell rallies, while the negative gamma pocket at 6770 (-4.8B) provides a floor where dealers buy dips to hedge short gamma positions. Given the current positioning just below the flip and the substantial stabilizing forces above, expect mean-reverting behavior with upside capped near 6800 and support emerging around 6770.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy trading between 6770-6800 with dealers providing liquidity at both extremes.",
